  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "These trackers achieve obvious performance advantages although the speed is low.",
    "Zhang et al. [74] proposed an end-to-end real-time RGB-T tracking framework with balanced accuracy.",
    "They applied ResNet [112] as the feature extractor and fused RGB and thermal information at the feature level, for target localization and box estimation.",
    "Attribute-driven representation network (ADRNet) [29] and challenge-aware tracker (CAT) [113] were proposed to exploit the effectiveness of attributespecific representation for object modeling.",
    "Both trackers contain several individual branches to mine attribute-specific properties, whereby those features are fused to build a powerful representation for accurate tracking.Based on the vision transformer [114,115], several transformer-based multi-modal trackers have been proposed [85][86][87] to exploit the complementary cues in both modalities."
